AB  - These pages are a brief contribution dedicated to the exploration of
the relevance of images for legal discourse. Considering the specific
field of road traffic regulation, the paper shows, starting from
Michel Foucault’s seminal research on the concept of “dispositive”,
how the use of images produced by visual devices such as surveillance
cameras or satellite navigators has gradually integrated legislation
mainly composed of “graphic rules” (road signs). A passage destined to
create a new order of an extra-legal nature that profoundly affects
the construction of new forms of subjectivity.

Keywords: Dispositive; Foucault; Visual rules; Agamben; Traffic signs

Index: 1. Was ist ein normatives Bild? – 2. What is a (optical)
dispositive? – 3. Omnes et singulatim: The power of the gaze –
