AB  - How have legal ideas and institutions affected Western culture? And
how has the law itself been shaped by its cultural context?In a work
spanning 4,500 years, these questions are addressed by 57 experts,
each contributing an authoritative study of a theme applied to a
period in history. Supported by detailed case material and over 230
illustrations, the volumes examine trends and nuances of the culture
of law in Western societies from antiquity to the present. This
chapter explores the role of police uniform in transforming the image
of policing in various regions between 1820-1920.
