AB  - In Legal Staging a group of lawyers and legal historians has tried to
identify the new Nordic legal map which is under construction. This
volume is a collection of papers addressing legal staging, and most of
the articles combine theoretical approaches to the visuality of law
with practical experiences and effects. The texts show that law is so
much more than law in action and law in books; law is also part of a
visual culture. It contributes to that culture and is, in turn,
analysed, maintained and criticised by that culture. At the same time,
the cultural manifestations of law change the way we understand law
and, thus, changes law itself.
