AB  - Law’s relationship to images has often been assumed or ignored but
until recently there have been few attempts to unravel the law-image
dynamic. Representations of law and legal phenomena in a range of
forms including sculpture, fine art, film, cartoons and street art
play a critical role in constructing and re-constructing ideological
hegemony and myths about law through the creation of a set of
permitted symbols. The challenge for socio-legal scholars is to
understand and interrogate these visual codes, interrogate how they
wield power and to plot the ways in which they are experienced on a
day to day basis.
