of legality that are different to modern law. There is a primal seeing
of law unmediated by reading, writing or possibly thinking. This
introduction identifies the primacy of the eye, the emergence of
visual jurisprudence and the transformations of law as a paper-based
material practice to a digitally enabled activity.
