AB  - My research is focused on the characteristics of the crime of theft
and its punishment in Eike von Repgowʼs Sachsenspiegel, which was
written between 1220 and 1235 in the Middle Low German language. The
relationship between the text and images in the four codices picturati
of this legal text will be examined in the context of some passages
directly related to theft and its punishment to demonstrate that the
illustrations in these manuscripts can contribute to a better
understanding of legal institutions in the German Middle Ages.
