AB  - A thirteenth-century Digestum vetus manuscript in the Library of the
Polish Academy of Sciences at Kornik (MS 824) contains hundreds of
marginal images added between and around the glosses, which have
various relationships with the text. The author discusses their
function not only as visual commentary, but also as mnemonic aids to
the reader. Some images pun on words or directly evoke an action
described in a passage; others constitute pictorial representations of
verbal tropes. As guiding signs or indications of content they direct
the reader’s attention to a passage of particular importance, mark its
location, and help to fix it in memory.
