AB  - The idea that guides this paper is that visual images of law have
contributed in a very important way to the creation of a mental image
of law that supports the belief in an obligation to obey the law. My
purpose is: first, to identify and to analyze the visual
representation of law and the messages they convey. Second, attempt to
find out how they shape the mental image we have of law by following
the construction of judicial space and, then, through the iconography
of law in order to understand how they build the belief that there is
an obligation to obey the law; hence the idea that law has authority.
