AB  - La Celestina is a breakthrough in the development of Spanish
narratives from educa-tional purposes towards multi-layered literary
worlds and thus crucial for the interac-tion between casuistry and
imaginative literature. The plot’s casualties are framed by
soliloquies referring to legal and ethical questions. On a rhetorical
level, law is present in the master trope of blind(folded) justice.
Combining a close reading of these soliloquies with contemporaneous
casuistical writings and an iconological search for evidences
elucidates the intention of this contested masterpiece.
