AB  - Emblems are visible metaphors, a synthesis of words and images. They
traditionally embodied simple earthly truths, moral standards, and
political principles. Emblem studies is a special historical
discipline studying symbolic representations of certain notions or
ideas. Scholars distinguish several sources of this discipline:
Egyptian hieroglyphics; epigrammatic, fabular, and numismatic heritage
of the Classical Antiquity; medieval fabliau and proverbs; bestiary
images of both epochs.
