AB  - Revolution in court; the visual and digital transformation of law The
variety and importance of visual displays in American courtrooms has
exploded. This visual and digital transformation of law practice
heralds nothing less than a revolution in the ways that lawyers argue,
jurors and judges decide, and the public thinks about the law. This
article offers essential background for understanding law's visual and
digital transformation. Also the ubiquity of digital technologies is
discussed. The authors conclude by outlining the challenges that these
features of digital culture pose for the law.
