AB  - Courts shape the rule of law. Their history is part of the culture of
a country. The way judicial institutions are treated characterises a
country's attitude towards the status they accord to courts and
judges. In its almost 400-year history, Bavaria's Supreme Court has
experienced all facets - from being held in high esteem to being
abolished twice. Its history is a lesson that points to the future in
the development of European legal culture.
