AB  - Illegalized immigration is a highly iconic topic. The public
perception of the current regime for mobility is profoundly shaped by
visual and verbal images. As the issue of illegalized immigration is
gaining increasing political momentum, the authors feel it is a
well-warranted undertaking to analyze the role of images in the
creation of illegalization. Their aim is to trace the visual processes
that produce these very categories. The authors aim to map out an
iconography of illegalized immigration in relation to political,
ethical, and aesthetic discourses.
