AB  - Legal iconological analysis of a large scale printed work by Belgian
artist Xavier Mellery (1845-1921). After a short biography of the
artist, this article describes the technical aspects of the artwork
(phototypie) and the commission Mellery got from the Federation des
avocats belges, in which Edmond Picard and Octave Maus played an
important role. The artwork was exposed on the occasion of an
important feast in thee newly built Brussels palace of justice. Copies
were exposed in almost all Belgian court houses. An earlier smaller
version of the composition was published in the Pandectes belges. The
article gives an iconographic description of the allegoric persons and
contextualizes the commission in the Brussels art and law scene of the
late nineteenth century.
