AB  - In early modern times, literary organisation, qualification and the
dissemination of technological knowledge increased by leaps and
bounds. Early textbooks on architecture and mechanics, as a special
species, played a major role in this development. SLUB, partly
incorporating holdings of TH/TU Dresden, possesses a remarkable number
of magnificently illustrated volumes. This paper analyses works of the
Renaissance artist-engineers and early theatri machinarum, as well as
the specialised technological literature of early period of
Enlightenment. As pictures have become ever more important sources for
historical research in the course of the so-called iconic turn, focus
is to be placed on the specific use of visualisations to fulfil
documentary, communicative, legitimising and epistemological
obligations.
