Spanish lawyer and historian Juan de Solorzano. A comparison of their
works reveals the extensive use the Spanish scholar made of the
Dutchman's book.

Solorzano's voluminous Emblemata centum deserves, therefore, a place
of honour in the history of both the reception of Junius' emblem book
and of Latin emblematic literature in general.
