AB  - This article examines some of the artistic creations of the late
Middle Ages in which the central theme is justice in the

afterlife in order to attempt to represent divine justice for the men
and women living in the territory of the diocese of Calahorra and La

Calzada in the late medieval period. It analyses the incorporation of
private justice in Christian ideology, the resurgence of millenarian

doctrine in the medieval period, and representations of justice in the
afterlife in the late Middle Ages.
