AB  - The general topic of this book, miscarried justice, is suggested by
the title's allusion to the sightlessness of the proverbial
representation of justice. Viewpoints from several academic
disciplines, e.g., philosophy, sociology, linguistics, criminal
justice, literary criticism, and religious studies, are brought
together with theories of law. This collection is not only
interdisciplinary but cross-cultural as well. The common language is
'legal semiotics', in both a Peircean and non-Peircean idiolect. This
collection is a rich, cross-referential research tool for
investigators of law and semiotics in all its aspects.
