AB  - The text represents one reading and interpretation of Werner Gephart’s
exhibition and intervention in 2016 at The Dickson Poon School of Law,
Kings College London. Professor Gephart’s exhibition challenged ideas
related to the law’s representation, investigating the way it is both
simultaneously omnipresent and invisible in society. As such, themes
like the refugee crisis and Brexit provided important contextual
references for the project while major metaphors related to the law,
such as 'bouche de la loi' (the mouth of the law) and 'das Auge des
Gesetzes' (the eye of the law).
