AB  - This article is about Images of Justice, where the Energy Metaphor
seems more adequate to understand the Gender Feminine and the
Masculine values of Justice. We emphasize the dualistic point of view
that organizes and bounds our perception of reality and the Images of
Justice, which implies both feminine and masculine values. It is
useful to reinforce the philosophical and legal arguments with
transdisciplinary fields, such as Psychology, Anthropology, Semiotics,
History and Theory of Art, Religious Imagery and on. We argument
through Images and Legends of Justice given in some different
Cultures, in order to get a broader perception of Justice, creating
repertoire beyond the written Tradition. The Synchronism between
personal experience and social fluency will be converged by some
Myths´ functions, both social and psychological. The article will be
settled with some Greek and Egyptian representations of Justice and
some Afro-American Imagery, which enables African Tradition after
syncretic Efforts.
