AB  - Some copies of the Decretum Gratiani were richly illustrated with
miniatures that allow us to study the image given of ecclesiastical
power. Throughout the 14th c. old and new issues were embodied in
representations accompanying the Causes and other texts included in
ancient compilations of canon law. The illustrations are a synthesis
that leads us into a complex world of relationships and theories in
which religious power is manifested and highlights the status
conferred on popes, cardinals and bishops. In the adoption of a
position the confrontation with other powers and social sectors is
essential. The analysis of one of these luxury manuscripts (London,
BL, ms. Add.15274-15275), linked to the workshop of Ferrer Bassa and
Catalan art most implicated in the search of the Italian Trecento, is
the main object of study of this article. Its narrative and its
textual and figurative complexities must be located and understood in
the time of the Avignon exile and the papacy of Pope Clement VI. It is
a work of ...
