AB  - The present essay concerns the relationship between law and cinema. In
particular, I shall introduce and discuss the following thesis: cinema
does not merely represent images of law, but, on the contrary, it
works as a practice of production of law as image, i.e. as what comes
to existence because of its appearance and visibility, and not because
of the fact of being «said», uttered. Cinema can thus be studied as a
procedure of creation of legal concepts, radically different from that
typical of juridical practice.
