AB  - The aim of this paper is to show the way in which the Siete Partidas
builds the images of the king and the emperor. The starting point to
understand the different treatment of these images is the disociation
produced by Alphonse’s legal discourse upon both institutions
(Monarchy and Empire) within the context of the Fecho del Imperio .
Thus, our proposal is to study the ways in which Alphonse, the Wise
king, builds the arguments of the laws that pretend to regulate these
institutions. Moreover, we will study the reception of this treatment
in the 16th century gloss of Gregorio Lopez.
